author: pbs.org
title: Migrant-magnet Sweden strains to shelter unexpected influx
text: Amid a major migration crisis, Sweden has received more refugees per capita than any other European country, and is proud of its open door policy. But the welcoming nation's immigration system is straining to meet the demand, which far exceeds what the government anticipated. Special correspondent Malcolm Brabant reports.
